{{- /* Newest compound-engineering-plugin release tag.

       The repo interleaves several tag trains (marketplace-*, cursor-marketplace-*,
       cli-*), so `gitHubLatestRelease` would eventually resolve to the wrong one —
       take the newest release whose tag carries the compound-engineering- prefix.

       Shared so the FOUR consumers of this plugin can never land on different
       releases — the extracted archive path is the same versioned local dir
       (~/.local/share/compound-engineering/v<semver>/), so every agent
       resolves to that same on-disk tree:
         - .chezmoiexternals/ai-agents.toml — the archive external's URL uses
           the raw tag (compound-engineering-v<semver>) and the target path
           uses v<semver> (front-half prefix stripped).
         - .chezmoitemplates/opencode-plugins-json.tmpl — renders the fully
           qualified plugin path into opencode.json.
         - .chezmoiscripts/00-tools/run_onchange_after_compound-engineering
           — prunes sibling versions under ~/.local/share/compound-engineering
           so only the current tag remains on disk.
         - .chezmoiscripts/70-agents/run_onchange_after_install-compound-engineering
           — registers the same versioned path with Claude Code, Codex, and pi
           (OpenCode is file-phase only; every ref bump also re-registers here
           because the marketplace path itself changed).
       Claude gains a proper pin here too: its `plugin marketplace add` takes no
       --ref, but a versioned LOCAL PATH is unambiguous.
    */ -}}
{{- range (gitHubReleases "everyinc/compound-engineering-plugin") -}}
{{-   if hasPrefix "compound-engineering-" .TagName -}}
{{-     .TagName -}}
{{-     break -}}
{{-   end -}}
{{- end -}}
